# PBR override lists

These files are loaded by `/usr/share/pbr/pbr.user.opencck-merged-vpn` during every PBR restart.

Priority:

1. Generated WAN-RU list -> `pbr_wan_4_dst_ip_user`.
   - IPv4/CIDR source: `https://www.ipdeny.com/ipblocks/data/aggregated/ru-aggregated.zone`
   - Domain source: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/v2fly/domain-list-community/master/data/category-ru`
2. `force-wan.*` -> `pbr_wan_4_dst_ip_user`.
3. Downloaded VPN list:
   - `https://antifilter.download/list/allyouneed.lst`
   - `https://iplist.opencck.org/ru/?format=text&data=cidr4`
4. `force-vpn.*` -> current `TARGET_INTERFACE` set, currently `awg2` unless `vpn1`/`vpn2` changes it.
5. `force-<interface>.*` -> matching `pbr_<interface>_4_dst_ip_user` set.

Files:

- `force-wan.domains`: domains that must go directly via WAN.
- `force-wan.ips`: IPv4/CIDR entries that must go directly via WAN.
- `force-wan.urls`: URL sources for IPv4/CIDR entries that must go directly via WAN.
- `force-vpn.domains`: domains that must go via the current tunnel.
- `force-vpn.ips`: IPv4/CIDR entries that must go via the current tunnel.
- `force-vpn.urls`: URL sources for IPv4/CIDR entries that must go via the current tunnel.
- `force-awg1.domains`, `force-proxyde.domains`, etc.: domains that must go via a specific PBR interface.

One entry per line. Comments start with `#`.

Local export from the control app:

```powershell
python tools\vpn_control_app.py export-pbr-overrides
```

The export currently includes global admin routes only. Per-user routes need source-IP matching and are intentionally not emitted into these global PBR sets.
